
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `hp-info` baraye gereftan etela'at dar bareye hardware va systeme karkonande HP (Hewlett-Packard) estefade mishavad. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ta model, version BIOS, serial number, va digar moshakhasate sakht afzari device HP khod ra bedanid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `hp-info` --> 📝 Namayesh etela'at asli hardware mesle model va serial number.
    🔹 `hp-info --bios` --> 💻 Namayesh etela'at BIOS mesle version.
    🔹 `hp-info --disk` --> 💽 Namayesh etela'at disk drive ha.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ hp-info

    🔹 Namayesh etela'at hardware asli

    $ hp-info --bios

    🔹 Namayesh etela'at BIOS

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ hp-info
    Product Name: HP ProBook 450 G7
    Serial Number: ABC123XYZ

    🔹 In mesal namayesh midahad ke dastoor `hp-info` name mahsool va serial number ra chap mikonad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `hp-info` command is used to retrieve information about HP (Hewlett-Packard) hardware and the operating system. This command helps you to find the model, BIOS version, serial number, and other hardware specifications of your HP device.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `hp-info` --> 📝 Display basic hardware information such as model and serial number.
    🔹 `hp-info --bios` --> 💻 Display BIOS information such as version.
    🔹 `hp-info --disk` --> 💽 Display disk drive information.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ hp-info

    🔹 Display basic hardware information.

    $ hp-info --bios

    🔹 Display BIOS information.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ hp-info
    Product Name: HP ProBook 450 G7
    Serial Number: ABC123XYZ

    🔹 This example shows that the `hp-info` command prints the product name and serial number.
